{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17658864","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17658864"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T22:57:00+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T22:57:00+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"20833"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"20833","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/20833"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"13708"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"97044"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"13708","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/13708"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"20833"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"79660"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"11660"},{"type":"tags","id":"11661"},{"type":"tags","id":"12658"},{"type":"tags","id":"12795"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"33007"},{"type":"contributions","id":"33008"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"97044","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/97044"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EHypoplasia refers to the underdevelopment of organs or tissues during development.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following findings most likely represents hypoplasia?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Brain with disorganised cortical layers","Liver with excessive fibrotic tissue","Kidneys with cystic malformation","Lungs with reduced weight and volume","Heart with abnormal valve leaflet structure"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct answer is \u003Cstrong\u003Elungs with reduced weight and volume\u003C/strong\u003E, which represents pulmonary hypoplasia. Hypoplasia refers to the underdevelopment or incomplete development of an organ or tissue due to a decreased number of cells. The reduced lung size and weight are characteristic findings in pulmonary hypoplasia.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained as follows:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBrain with disorganised cortical layers\u003C/strong\u003E represents cortical dysplasia, a condition where neurons fail to migrate properly during development, resulting in disorganised architecture rather than simple underdevelopment.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELiver with excessive fibrotic tissue\u003C/strong\u003E represents fibrosis or cirrhosis, which is a pathological process involving tissue damage and scarring, not a developmental underdevelopment.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EKidneys with cystic malformation\u003C/strong\u003E represents renal dysplasia, which is an abnormal development of tissue with disorganised cellular arrangement, not simply underdevelopment.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHeart with abnormal valve leaflet structure\u003C/strong\u003E represents a cardiac malformation or dysplasia, which involves abnormal tissue organisation rather than just reduced development.\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHypoplasia specifically refers to the underdevelopment of an organ that otherwise has normal structure and cellular organisation. This differs from aplasia (complete absence of an organ) and dysplasia (abnormal cellular organisation within a tissue).\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Hypoplasia is the underdevelopment or incomplete development of a tissue or organ.","Pulmonary hypoplasia involves underdevelopment of the lungs, often secondary to conditions that restrict lung growth.","Hypoplasia differs from aplasia 